{"key":"processedPost-13700040","value":{"id":13700040,"first":13700020,"last":13700186,"when":1293641736,"utime":"12/29/10 06:55 PM","content":"That isn't the correct type of humidifier.&nbsp; Get one with a spinning impeller, not a wicking filter.&nbsp; The type you have will never get above 60% to 70%.<br /><br />Get rid of the fogger.&nbsp; You want humidity, not fog which is total saturation.<br /><br />Put the correct coolmist humidifier on the floor of the unit beside the shelves so it can shoot upward.&nbsp; Humid air is less dense than dry air, thus it rises.&nbsp; If you put your humidifier on a top shelf, that's where the humidity will stay.<br /><br />Leaving the bottom open is always good for fresh air supply, but cut some openings in the top of the greenhouse too so air can circulate.&nbsp; The CO2 won't 'drain' out the bottom because it's mixed with the air.<br />RR","title":"Re: RH issues in mini greenhouse","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}